text:
1-13 Fair Street, north side, east from Prince Street, to Fleet Place. The view in the background, is 91-99 Fleet Place, east side, between Myrtle Ave., and Willoughby Street.

October 31, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

Fair Street (left), east from Price Street to Fleet Place, showing a row of colonial homes. Fair Street is a short, one-block narrow thoroughfare connecting Prince and Fleet, the homes being on the north side of the street and south side being a clearance. The buildings in the right background are on the east side of Fleet Street.

P. L. Sperr
October 31, 1927
